'''USS ''Little Rock'' (LCS-9)''' is a {{sclass-|Freedom|littoral combat ship}} of the [[United States Navy]].<ref name="NVR Little Rock" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fox11online.com/dpp/news/local/north_counties/marinette-marine-to-build-uss-little-rock |title=Marinette Marine to build USS Little Rock |date=15 July 2011 |publisher=Fox News |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718130928/http://www.fox11online.com/dpp/news/local/north_counties/marinette-marine-to-build-uss-little-rock |archivedate=18 July 2011 }}</ref> It is the second ship named after [[Little Rock]], the capital city of [[Arkansas]].<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.defense.gov/releases/release.aspx?releaseid=14656 |title=Navy Names Littoral Combat Ship Little Rock |date=15 July 2011 |number=616-11 |publisher=U.S. Department of Defense |accessdate=19 April 2015}}</ref> The ship will cost somewhere between $300 million and $350 million<ref>{{cite news|publisher=Fox 11 |title=Future USS Detroit launched at Marinette Marine shipyard |first=Gabrielle |last=Mays |date=18 October 2014 |url=http://fox11online.com/2014/10/18/marinette-marine-to-launch-uss-detroit/ |accessdate=19 April 2015}}</ref> and is said{{by whom?|date=August 2015}} to have many new features.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Breaking Defense |title=USS Little Rock, From Light to Guided Missile Cruiser: Lessons For The Littoral Combat Ship, |first=Norman |last=Friedman |date=23 December 2013 |url=http://breakingdefense.com/2013/12/uss-little-rock-from-light-to-guided-missile-cruiser-lessons-for-the-littoral-combat-ship/ |accessdate=19 April 2015}}</ref> The [[keel]] laying ceremony for ''Little Rock'' was on 27 June 2013. The mast stepping ceremony took place on 23 April 2015, followed by the [[Ship naming and launching|christening]] ceremony on 18 July 2015. ''Little Rock'' is presently undergoing sea trials.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}} The ship will be [[Ship commissioning|commissioned]] at [[Buffalo, New York]] in late 2016 or early 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.buffalonews.com/city-region/new-uss-little-rock-to-be-commissioned-in-buffalo-20160426 |title=New USS Little Rock to be commissioned at Canalside |work=The Buffalo News |last=Besecker |first=Aaron |date=26 April 2016 |accessdate=26 April 2016}}</ref>
